rComments: If you can take the bike version of this class, DO IT. Yes, you have many readings to do over the summer, but it's probably one of the best experiences i've ever had in uni. we went biking (11 students and Jean) from montreal to quebec city and visited SO MANY translation agencies and learned so much more than we would've learned in a classroom.

Jean cares for his students and wants to know more about you than your student number. There was a lot of material to cover at home, but the midterm was easy  if you did the tests he put on blackboard every week, and read the material he gave. There was no textbook, which was nice because we all have other textbooks to buy!

Professor gives way too much reading material, and by too much, I mean he expects us to read a couple hundred pages per week. The exams are way out there and there is no way to prepare for them. If you can avoid this prof, you should go ahead and do that.

Excellent teacher, really knows his stuff. Explains well, incredible mastery of the French language. A joy to listen to. Energetic, positive. Also had him in Documentation et lexicologie. Both classes excellent.
